## Overview

GPA Goal Planner is a Streamlit web app that calculates the minimum Q4 and final exam scores you need across your courses to hit a target GPA. It supports weighted and unweighted GPA, AP/Honors/CP course levels, and can import grade data directly from Google Sheets exports.

---

## How It Works

1. You enter your classes with Q1–Q3 and midterm (E1) grades already completed.
2. You set a goal GPA.
3. The app runs a **greedy spillover algorithm** that figures out the minimum remaining scores (Q4 + Final Exam average) needed per class to reach your goal.
4. Results are shown as a per-course plan, ranked from easiest to hardest improvement.

---

## Grade Weight System

Each course's final percentage is calculated from six components:

| Component | Weight | Notes |
|-----------|--------|-------|
| Q1 | 22% | Quarter 1 |
| Q2 | 22% | Quarter 2 |
| Q3 | 22% | Quarter 3 |
| Q4 | 22% | Quarter 4 |
| E1 (Midterm) | 6% | Mid-year exam |
| F1 (Final Exam) | 6% | End-of-year exam |

**Completed (Q1+Q2+Q3+E1) = 72%**
**Remaining (Q4+F1) = 28%**

The planner optimizes over the remaining 28% — specifically the *average* of Q4 and F1, referred to as the **remainder** (`X`).

---

