## Importing from Google Sheets

1. Open your grade sheet in Google Sheets.
2. Go to **File → Download → Comma-separated values (.csv)**.
3. Upload via the sidebar uploader.

Column names are mapped flexibly:

| Recognized aliases | Canonical field |
|--------------------|----------------|
| `grade`, `yr`, `year` | Grade |
| `class`, `course`, `subject` | Class |
| `q1`, `quarter 1` | Q1 |
| `q2`, `q 2`, `quarter 2` | Q2 |
| `e1`, `midterm`, `midyear` | E1 |
| `q3`, `q 3`, `quarter 3` | Q3 |
| `q4`, `q 4`, `quarter 4` | Q4 |
| `f1`, `f 1`, `final` | F1 |
| `type`, `level`, `course type` | Level |
| `weight`, `credits`, `cr` | Credits |
| `grade #`, `course %`, `avg` | Course % |

Cells containing `FALSE`, `N/A`, `-`, or empty strings are treated as blank. Rows with `Doesn't Count` as their type are excluded from GPA calculations but kept in the table.

